 Integrated with GitHub Actions for automated deployment of infrastructure changes.  \n**Key Trade-offs:**  \n-   **Complexity:** Microservices introduce operational complexity (monitoring, debugging, deployment coordination), mitigated by strong CI/CD and observability.  \n-   **Cost:** Managed services like RDS and Fargate can be more expensive than self-managing, but the reduction in operational overhead and increased reliability justified the cost.  \n-   **Learning Curve:** The team needed to learn new AWS services and Terraform best practices. We invested in training and pair programming.  \nThis approach resulted in a highly scalable, fault-tolerant, and observable platform, significantly improving developer velocity and reducing incident frequency."
